{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1509058532,"nonce":"9tmnud9rU5hifuyDFB8XsWvKH9s=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyNjg5MzcyMTI=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1539","origin":"github"},"title":"Create tool to clean up fastq reads with inconsistent @ and + lines","message":"Tool would do what is explained here: https://galaxyproject.org/support/ncbi-sra-fastq/#inconsistent-sequence-and-quality-identifiers\n\n - Make the tool smart enough to notice if the input is truncated and produce a human readable error that states that was detected, not just error with stack trace because the sequence and qual are not the same length or some part of a full fastq record is missing.\n - If the problem is internal to the file - give the line number where this was found along with the last read-in sequence identifier to give users a good way to find/fix the problem.\n - Same for internal extra blank lines - error with that noted (happens when multiple samples are merged sometimes). Or give option on form to users to ignore when that comes up, process the file, and optionally add that to a report.\n\n**Bonus**: Include option to split interlaced fastq data (all cleanup described on that hub page done in one step). The de-interlacer only works with reads ending with /1 and /2. Not all interlaced fastq is formatted that way (tends to come up when input is not sourced from NCBI).\n\n - Could just split every-other read as a default (\"I'm feeling lucky\")\n - Or force choice of format OR include \"Advanced options\" to allow user to specify the format with a regular expression (include examples from the above linked hub FAQ)\n  - Tool shouldn't assume 1/2 Illumina 1.8+ identifiers - some might be 1/3\n  - Include option to filter out/write out missing parts of \"pairs\" to optional output files (couldn't be used with default every-other read split)\n  - Include option to add on or modify /1 /2 or R1/R2 to end of sequence identifiers to help with building collection pairs.\n\n\n**Bonus2:** Option to output a summary log file with counts for inputs/outputs would be great. Including a length distribution as well (shortest, longest, mean, stddev, Q1-Q4) would make the report even better. Including detected problems that were ignored or skipped over or triggered a failure would be A++.\n\nPut this in tool group _QC Manipulation_ AND in _NCBI Tools_ so is easy to find\n\ncc @nekrut","files":null}]}